articles.author: Nidal Al-Mughrabi, Dawoud Abu Alkas
articles.description: An Israeli military strike killed 12 people in a house in Gaza City early on Saturday, bringing the death toll from strikes across Gaza to 62 over the last day, Palestinian medics said, as mediators launched a new ceasefire push in Qatar.
articles.title: Israeli strikes kill dozens in Gaza Strip as new ceasefire talks begin

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: South Korean investigators again asked the country's acting president on Saturday to order the presidential security service to comply with an arrest warrant for impeached President Yoon Suk Yeol.
articles.title: South Korea investigators ask acting president to clear way for Yoon's arrest

articles.author: Hyunjoo Jin
articles.description: Park Chong-jun who reports directly to  impeached President Yoon Suk Yeol, was instrumental in rebuffing investigators' attempt to serve an arrest warrant on Yoon.
articles.title: Head of South Korea Yoon's security finds himself in spotlight

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Russian rescue workers have cleared more than 86,000 metric tons of contaminated sand and earth on either side of the Kerch Strait following an oil spill in the Black Sea last month, the emergencies ministry said on Saturday.
articles.title: Russia clears thousands of tons of contaminated sand after Black Sea oil spill

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Russia denies using gas as a weapon to coerce Moldova, and blames Kyiv for refusing to renew a gas-transit deal.
articles.title: Moldova breakaway region to face new power cuts on Saturday, officials say

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Russian forces continue to launch attacks near the Ukrainian city of Pokrovsk in an effort to bypass it from the south and cut off supply routes to Ukraine's troops, the Ukrainian military said on Saturday.
articles.title: Russia attacks strategic city of Pokrovsk aiming to cut off supply lines, Kyiv military says

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Talks between the two biggest centrist parties in Austria on forming a coalition government without the far-right Freedom Party (FPO) have collapsed, Chancellor Karl Nehammer said on Saturday, adding that he would step down in the coming days.
articles.title: Austrian coalition talks collapse, chancellor to step down

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: King Charles passed on condolences to Edward Pettifer's family, a source said.
articles.title: Briton killed in New Orleans attack was stepson of former royal nanny

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Ukrainian President Volodymyr Zelenskiy said on Saturday that Russian and North Korean forces suffered heavy losses in fighting in Russia's southern Kursk region.
articles.title: Ukraine's Zelenskiy: Heavy Russian, North Korean losses in Russia's Kursk region

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Italian Prime Minister Giorgia Meloni is flying to Florida where she will meet President-elect Donald Trump, Italian media reported on Saturday.
articles.title: Italian PM Meloni flying to US to meet Trump, Italian media report
